Source: picamera
Maintainer: Dave Hughes <dave@waveform.org.uk>
Homepage: http://pypi.python.org/pypi/picamera
Section: python
Priority: extra
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 8), dh-python, python-all (>= 2.7), python-setuptools, python3-all, python3-setuptools, python-docutils, python-sphinx (>= 1.0.7+dfsg-1~)
Standards-Version: 3.9.3
X-Python-Version: >= 2.7
X-Python3-Version: >= 3.2

Package: python-picamera
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${python:Depends}
Suggests: python-picamera-docs
Description: A pure Python interface to the Raspberry Pi's camera module.
 picamera is a library for working with the Raspberry Pi's camera module from
 within Python without having to resort to subprocesses. The majority of the
 functionality of raspistill and raspivid is replicated by the library.
 .
 This is the Python 2 version of the package.

